This paper deals with the problem of selecting a learning algorithm and setting its hyperparameters, which is a core problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a fully automated approach using Bayesian optimization, which is a popular technique in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also deals with datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Data Mining). Finally, the use of Bayesian optimization suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
